    org.moddingx.libx.mod.ModXRegistration.registerMulti(ResourceKey<? extends Registry<T>>, String, MultiRegisterable<T>)
    MultiRegisterable is deprecated. See there for more information
    org.moddingx.libx.registration.MultiRegisterable
    To register multiple elements at the same time, use a regular Registerable add register the additional elements in Registerable.registerAdditional(RegistrationContext, Registerable.EntryCollector). For the use in ModInit, use PlainRegisterable. This way, it's possible to for example put Items and containers registering 16 items, one for each color in the same class annotated ith RegisterClass.
